3 ways to protect our sensitive information

1. Systems Manager
2. Secret Manager
3. Hashi crop voult

1. Systems manager to store the data in parameter wise like key and value, store sensitive information by using systems manager we can do cost optimization, secret manager will change very high
2. Secret manager to store very highly sensitive data like DB passwords and by using secret manager we can rotate certificates or passwords evey 90 days or 180 days based on our requirements.
3. Hashi corp voult: maily if your organization using multi cloud , then we should go for hashi corp voult and also it's provides lot of features
